 If You Rescue Me  is a brilliant easy-listening, smooth and calming track guaranteed to delight. It is sung by actors Gael Garcia Bernal, Alain Chabat, Sacha Bourdo, and actress Aur lia Petit while they are dressed as cats. Their instruments are made of yarn and cardboard, a Gondry trademark.','',2,'21.mp3','0uWahGBJPTINwyE1Y5TVMg',170800,26,'2020-11-03T09:25:05Z');

Just some small and ordinary stories, but they are very beautiful and fascinating. They can happen in any city in the world, and they are happening all the time. 

This song is from Feist. It starts at the end of the movie. 

When I just heard it, when all the stories became many small pictures on the screen, it felt like long ago I just heard The Lady In Red, or Rain And Tears. But We  re All In The Dance is not that disconsolate, and is more warm and calm. 

It fits the movie very well. Life is always going on and though the wound is hard to heal and the scars run deep, it can still be cured some day. Some people leave and will never come back again. Something we miss out will just be a pity forever. But nobody can stop life from moving on. 

And I think, maybe we can watch this movie again with someone special in our heart, drink some nice red wine at the same time, and dance a bit when this song starts. Then that night would be wonderful. 

